{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643908"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:59:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:59:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18022"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18022","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18022"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10736"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73312"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10736","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10736"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18022"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58783"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24984"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24986"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24998"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73312","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73312"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe trapezius is a large muscle covering the upper back and its main function is to stabilise the scapula and to control movements of the shoulder and upper limb.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following boundaries does the anterior border of this muscle form?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anterior border of the posterior triangle","Inferior border of the posterior triangle","Lateral border of the anterior triangle","Posterior border of the posterior triangle","Superior border of the anterior triangle"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe neck is divided into two main triangles: the anterior and posterior triangles. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior border of the posterior triangle\u003C/strong\u003E is formed by the anterior border of the trapezius muscle. This triangle is clinically significant as it contains important structures such as the accessory nerve, brachial plexus, and parts of the subclavian artery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior triangle\u003C/strong\u003E is bordered by the midline of the neck, the anterior border of the sternocleidomastoid muscle, and the inferior border of the mandible. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral border of the anterior triangle\u003C/strong\u003E is not formed by the trapezius but by the sternocleidomastoid muscle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior border of the posterior triangle\u003C/strong\u003E is formed by the posterior border of the sternocleidomastoid muscle, not the trapezius.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einferior border of the posterior triangle\u003C/strong\u003E is formed by the clavicle, not the trapezius.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The anterior border of the trapezius muscle forms the posterior boundary of the posterior triangle of the neck.","Understanding the anatomical boundaries of neck triangles is crucial for clinical assessments and surgical procedures."],"references":["Fehrenbach, M. J., \u0026 Herring, S. W. (2015). Illustrated Anatomy of the Head and Neck-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534836/","Cramer, G. D., \u0026 Darby, S. A. (2013). Clinical anatomy of the spine, 